name: Pharmachoice Building
directions: Second floor, end of the hall. Has urinal and toilet.
comment: There are other unisex accessible bathrooms in this building, on different floors as well.

name: Whitfield Hall
directions: Building entrance at porch around back. Downstairs to the right of the stairs. I was in the women's bathroom and it had extra pads and tampons.
comment: Probably need to be in hall for a reason, though might be able to stop and ask to use the restroom.

name: Copenhagen Central Station
street: 22 Reventlovsgade Ved Tivolis Hovedindgang 1577 1577 V., Bernstorffsgade 16,
directions: Near Starbucks and the main entrance
comment: Costs a fee of 5 DKR (you can pay with banking card or bar). They have large unisex stalls and a seperate room with urinals.

name: Lebanon Coop
directions: Back behind cafe/deli.

name: Vermont Commission on Women
directions: 2nd floor at top of front stairway.  Building accessible to the public from 7:45 am - 4:30 pm.

name: American Legion
directions: 1st floor in back next to back accessible enterance.
comment: Building open to public from 7:45 a.m. - 4:30 p.m. Weekdays.

name: Barbican Cinem
directions: In the pit cinema

name: Starbucks (Clay Terrace)
directions: In the hallway to the right of the counter
comment: If you use the side entrance (the door closest to the Qdoba) it's really easy to slip in and out without drawing attention. Also this is in a strip mall so people use this bathroom without buying anything all the time.

name: Playdate SEA
directions: Private restroom to the left in back near play structure.
comment: Free admission after 5pm on Mondays. Must be with children.

name: Culver's

name: Chipotle

name: Pep Boys

name: May's Cafe

name: Faces

name: Aura Coffee
directions: In the back to the left.

name: Stanley Park

name: The College of Wooster - Common Grounds ( Gable House)
directions: There is an all-gender restroom in Common Grounds.
comment:
Operating hours are Mon-Thurs 7pm-11 pm and Fri-Sat 8pm-12am. Common Grounds is a student-run and managed coffee house located in Gable House on College Ave. The majority of the members in Common Grounds have been through Safe Zone training.
https://www.wooster.edu/students/organizations/special/common/

name: Westminster Presbyterian Church
